After following our “asset‐based” approach – by adding together the beginning balances in cash, bank, and fixed assets and then “rolling forward” the effects of the operating transactions (including increases from receivables and sales profit and decreases from expenses and depreciation) – the overall calculation comes out with an initial asset total of 13,000,000.00 and a final asset balance of 13,216,409.49.

The final answer is:

